<div id="review_122257426" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/122257426" />
    <a title="Zachary Martin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4273820-zachary-martin"><img alt="Zachary Martin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1284653570p2/4273820.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/122257426?book_show_action=true">Sep 18, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Zachary Martin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Zachary Martin" href="/user/show/4273820-zachary-martin">Zachary Martin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4273820-zachary-martin?shelf=lit-crit">lit-crit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer122257426" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer828603904571609705">As a writer, I think this book of essays is bad for a person&apos;s soul. Franzen is a good writer, the arguments are interesting, and I would have a hard time denying he isn&apos;t on to something. For me, however, that something is a cynicism I find rather toxic. Ultimately, though I think his insistence that anything that doesn&apos;t stick to the Charles Dickens/Henry James model of the novel to be a waste of the readers time is about the most insecure reaction to experimental fiction going. I really liked</span>
  <span id="freeText828603904571609705" style="display:none">As a writer, I think this book of essays is bad for a person's soul. Franzen is a good writer, the arguments are interesting, and I would have a hard time denying he isn't on to something. For me, however, that something is a cynicism I find rather toxic. Ultimately, though I think his insistence that anything that doesn't stick to the Charles Dickens/Henry James model of the novel to be a waste of the readers time is about the most insecure reaction to experimental fiction going. I really liked the Corrections, I am interested to read Freedom someday, but I really don't like the Franzen who is always trying to distance himself from world of avant-garde writing while at the same time demanding his work be considered high art; this is real pretentiousness. </span>
  <a data-text-id="828603904571609705" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


